<br>
If you were to take a poll of Americans and ask if the USSR was communist, you'd probably get 99% saying it was.  We grew up here fighting communism in the form of the Soviet Union.  We prayed in our churches (those of us who were catholic) against communism in Russia.<br>
<br>
I think that the term communism has evolved well beyond what the definition originally was, and by the more accepted and standard use of the word, the USSR most definitely was communist.<br>
